NOOP¶

This is the interface for an object store. It can be used for testing inside other libraries to ensure the system works well in isolation.

list_buckets[source]

list_buckets(**kw)

List buckets, using the keywords to create a filter, limit, and order.

For NOOP, provide a buckets key to get a test set back.

find_or_create_bucket[source]

find_or_create_bucket(**kw)

Find or create a bucket, returning the bucket. Use the keywords to name the bucket.

For NOOP, provide a bucket to get a test bucket back.

remove_bucket[source]

remove_bucket(**kw)

Find and remove a bucket, if found. Use the keywords to name the bucket.

For NOOP, provide a bucket to get a test bucket back.

find_items[source]

find_items(**kw)

Find items in a bucket, returning a list of items. Use the keywords to name the bucket as well as filter, limit, and order the items.

For NOOP, provide an items key to get a test set back.

put[source]

put(**kw)

Put an item in a bucket, returning the status and the item.

For NOOP, provide an item key to get a test item back.

get[source]

get(**kw)

Find an item in a bucket, returning the item if found. Use the keywords to name the bucket as well as filter or name the item.

For NOOP, provide an item key to get a test item back.

remove[source]

remove(**kw)

Remove an item from a bucket, if found, returning a status. Use the keywords to name the bucket as well as filter or name the item.

For NOOP, provide a status key to get a test status back.

assert list_buckets() == []
assert list_buckets(buckets='buckets') == 'buckets'

assert find_or_create_bucket() is None
assert find_or_create_bucket(bucket='bucket') == 'bucket'

assert remove_bucket() is None
assert remove_bucket(bucket='bucket') == 'bucket'

assert find_items() == []
assert find_items(items='items') == 'items'

assert put() is None
assert put(item='item') == 'item'

assert get() is None
assert get(item='item') == 'item'

assert remove() is None
assert remove(status='status') == 'status'
